727819f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 70th Road
727819f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, south from 70th Road. The Boulevard
Bank occupies a aaall triangular block bounded by the Boule-
vard, 70th Road, and 108th Street.
P. L. Sperr  May 30, 1939

727818f-a.title: Queens: Queens Boulevard - 70th Road
727818f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard (trolley lines thereon), west from 70th Road
(extreme left), showing in the background a remodeled house occupied
at one time by Chas. Reitenback,a blackamith; Van Wicklen was the
owner in 1891.
August 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
